		"components": [],
		"description": "When creating a widget it is common to have more than one view, style, controller set.  Given the nature of a widget the elements would share a common style.  However there is no current way to define a \"widget wide\" tss file as there is with the \"app wide\" app.tss file.\r\n\r\nThis means that the author has two choose between two poor coding techniques;\r\n\r\n- Duplicate the common styles for each tss file within the widget\r\n- Pollute the app.tss solely for the benefit of the widget/\r\n\r\nThis reduces the ability for a widget to fulfil the part of its original goal which was to be DRY and re-usable.  The above problem highlights the lack or restrictions of re-usability.",
		"attachment": [],
		"flagged": false,
		"summary": "Add a \"widget wide\" tss file that serves as the base for the widget (think app.tss for app wide)",
